defaultfound out how crime figures could be massaged. Every Saturday there 
defaultwas a
default local market opposite Southall 
defaultpolice station 
defaultwhere dippers (pickpockets) would frequently be in action.
default6). 
defaultMembers of the public used to form queues 
defaultthat stretched 
defaultoutside the police station to report their wallets and purses stolen. Our instructions 
defaultas constables, 
defaultwere to report the loss as a theft
default only if the victim
defaults
default actually felt or saw their property being removed. If, as in most cases, they were unaware of the removal of their property, it was recorded as ‘Property Lost in the Street’ thus avoiding an unwelcome 
defaultaddition to the crime figures.
default7).
default 
defaultAnother controversial ‘massage tool’ was in respect of attempted burglaries. When burglars left ‘jemmy marks’ around window and door locks where they had attempted to break in but failed, the classification of the more serious ‘attempted burglary’ would b
defaulte downgraded to a more palatable and less serious offence of criminal damage. The same would be true where a window was smashed in an 
defaultattempt to get at the door or window lock.
