default11). 
defaultAcross London and doubtless elsewhere, officers normally of Detective Inspector rank, will pour over crime reports ostensibly to supervise them. In 
defaultactual fact they will be looking to ‘no crime’ or to reduce the classification to a serious offence illustrated above.
default 
defaultAnother trick of the trade is to send the statutory, ‘We are sorry you have been the victim of crime’ letter and then after the letter ha
defaults been sent, to reclassify the reported crime as ‘no crime.’
default The victim will still have his crime number in case of an insurance claim.
